data.title: Maria Caroline, Archduchess of Austria (1825
data.meta_description: Carte-de-vistie three quarter length studio portrait of Maria Caroline, Archduchess Rainer of Austria. The subject is shown in three quarter view, facing towards the left of the image. On the left hand side of the scene is a wooden writing desk. The Archduchess hair is elaborately arranged in plaits and a chignon, decorated with a black ribbon. She is wearing a highly decorated dress with a bustle, featuring a white ruffled yoke and fan cuffs. The main bodice and sleeves of the dress feature...
